A '''[[spiral galaxy]]''' is a type of [[galaxy]] characterized by a central [[bulge (astronomy)|bulge]] of old [[stellar population|Population II]] [[star]]s surrounded by a rotating disc of younger [[stellar population|Population I]] stars. A spiral galaxy maintains its [[spiral galaxy#Spiral arms|spirals arms]] due to [[Density wave theory]]
==Spiral galaxies==
